                <h1>From faculty to students, how the podcast movement has taken Duke</h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/3c44d475-57f7-40e1-8eb5-6f0829d7864b.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="&lt;p&gt;The&#x20;Sanford&#x20;School&#x20;of&#x20;Public&#x20;Policy&#x20;sponsors&#x20;a&#x20;number&#x20;of&#x20;podcasts,&#x20;including&#x20;&quot;Policy&#x20;360&quot;&#x20;and&#x20;&quot;Ways&#x20;and&#x20;Means.&quot;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;" class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            <p>The Sanford School of Public Policy sponsors a number of podcasts, including "Policy 360" and "Ways and Means."</p>

                                                             <aside class="photo-caption photo-credit d-block pl-1">
                                    <figcaption class="d-block">
                                                                                    Photo by <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/chronicle-file-photo-59c27007451b7">Chronicle File Photo</a> |
                                                                                                                                The Chronicle
                                                                            </figcaption>
                                </aside>
                            
                        </div>
                    </figure>
                
                                    <div class="row  mt-4 mb-0 mb-md-4">
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                            <aside class="author-name">
                                    
    
                                    
            By <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/selena-qian">Selena Qian</a>
                                    
                                <div class="mt-1">
                                    <span class="can-localize">September 20, 2017 | 9:11am EDT</span>
                                </div>
                            </aside>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 text-left text-md-right d-print-none">
                            <ul class="social-links list-unsyled list-inline mt-4 mt-md-0">
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2017/09/from-faculty-to-students-how-the-podcast-movement-has-taken-duke" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-facebook"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2017/09/from-faculty-to-students-how-the-podcast-movement-has-taken-duke&amp;text=From faculty to students, how the podcast movement has taken Duke" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="twitter" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a></li>
